Genetic Algorithms, Theory. 

Genetic Algorithms: The paper presents computational results from a high level parallel Genetic Algorithm that utilizes the method of stripe decomposition for assigning processors to tasks associated with the cells of a rectangular uniform grid. 

Theory: The paper presents a theoretical analysis of the method of stripe decomposition and proves that under some mild assumptions, as the problem size grows large in all parameters, the error bound associated with this feasible solution approaches zero.
